<br>
Where does it say that charm is supposed to be a carnage machine like it is now.  Tons of posts in this thread have correctly pointed out flaws but let me bring up one last thing.<br>
<br>
DC is NOT useless in tier 3 zones.  First, once you've DC'ed have your cleric buff the snot out of it.  After that it probably has in excess of 10k HP.  Give it two weapons and SoV.  Even against a level 65 mob your level 46 pets is a 10k tank doing over 100dps.  If your MT bites the big one you have a more than ample substitute until the rez.  Heck I'd even say that that pet alone with the right support could act as MT in many groups especially with slow.<br>
<br>
So pray tell how isn't using DC VERY balanced and powerful in a full group situation?  Can you solo with it in BoT? No.  Should you be able to solo mini bosses in the first place?  IMO no.<br>
<br>
Enchanters are the kings of indirect damge and damage mitigation.  A DC pet in addition to all the indirect damage you put out and damage mitigation you provide is more than sufficient; and if you don't think so I'm very sorry. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izelin>Izelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 3:52:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=115>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: charm</span><hr size=1> Thats great Soul, tell me how am I supposed to take the pet though the portals?   FYI,  You cant and no chanters cant summon DC pets to you, they get stuck.  So basically if I DC a pet I cant bring it with me anywhere I go like mages, im very limited to where a pet can go, and its an hour and 10 minutes if I lose it. <br>
