<br>
I would tend to agree, I am sure SoE meant for you to be able to charm but I think they overlooked the pure damage output of mobs in PoP.  The damage output of mobs has jumped at least twice as much as Luclin.<br>
<br>
Adding a damage cap upon charmed mobs would address that imbalance, then fix the few broken named mobs that can be solo farmed with charm (BoT for example) and charm would be fine.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Lower the level - We have that already its called Beckon, would be the same as removing the spell</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Actually I am betting that CoD was never intended as a sustainable charm but was meant as an upgrade to Dictate.  Thus giving Chanters a strong all purpose charm and a time restrictive verison for raiding.<br>
